  "description": "Electrical Discharge Machining (wire EDM ±2μm, sinker EDM), Computer Numerical Control (servo-driven axes, 5-axis machining, ±1μm positioning), and precision/ultra-precision grinding (0.01μm Ra surface finish). These technologies break through conventional machining limits to achieve the sub-micron precision required for semiconductor equipment: wafer stages, lens molds, and IC packaging molds.",
